                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d355">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 355.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Langston</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 13, 1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 339.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of your No. 717, of the
                    25th ultimo, respecting the case of Mr. Van Bokkelen, who is still confined in
                    the military hospital at Port-au-Prince, pending the determination by the court
                    of cassation of the question as to his right to make an assignment of his
                    property for the benefit of his creditors, I have to request you to promptly
                    inform this Department of the nature of the decision as soon as it is made known
                    by the court.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
